  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UN Plan of Action on the Safety of Journalists and the Issue of Impunity implemented, including commemoration of the International Day to End Impunity for Crimes Against Journalists (IDEI)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As lead coordinator of the UN Plan of Action on the Safety of Journalists, UNESCO will implement, together with partners, a range of activities to promote the safety of journalists through awareness-raising; standard-setting and policy advice; monitoring and reporting; capacity building; academic research; and partnership building. Areas of focus will include: training of law enforcement actors and the judiciary on freedom of expression; supporting regional, national and local mechanisms for the safety of journalists; and addressing the specific risks faced by women journalists. 

The commemoration of IDEI (2 November) will constitute a cornerstone of UNESCO&apos;s awareness-raising efforts on the safety of journalists.</narrative>
  </description>
